e actually enrolled in the pre-k, I was trying to help out the school by passing out budget info, so despite my deep concerns, I feel I am both passively (via property taxes) and actively (canvassing to get the damn budget passed) supporting the school I'm not convinced my kids should attend. &#10;You know what has yet to face any serious scrutiny during these ongoing budget disasters? The god damn football program in my school district. To me, that is a HUGE problem with the 'education system' some seem to think I'm not suporting if I choose to homeschool. &#10;2) Kerfuffle is one of my top 3 all time favorite words. I love it. I even love saying it.&#10;As I type, I'm saying...&#10;Kerfuffle...Keeeeerrrrrrrrrrrrfuffle!&#10;3) I'm nodding in agreement as I read ninja's and college mommy's posts. I'm still researching school options and my wife and I discuss it constantly... but it's posts like theirs that completely turned my notions about homeschooling upside down. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1265" language="en" documentId="616" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Semi-Crunchy-Dad" date="09/05/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=30" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="616" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="38"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="39" end="597"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="598" end="863"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="864" end="954"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="955" end="979"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="980" end="1017"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="1018" end="1265"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>